# React Component Conventions

## File structure

Each component lives in its own folder:

```
ComponentName/
  ComponentName.tsx          # Implementation
  ComponentName.module.scss  # Colocated SCSS module
  index.ts                   # Barrel export: export { ComponentName } from './ComponentName';
```

Use **named exports** for components (except `App` which is a default export).

## Framer Motion

All entrance animations use the shared easing curve `[0.22, 1, 0.36, 1]` for consistency.

Staggered reveals use small incremental delays (`delay: i * 0.06`). Keep durations short (0.3–0.5s).

```tsx
<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, x: -20 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, x: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.35, delay: i * 0.06, ease: [0.22, 1, 0.36, 1] }}
>
```

## Accessibility

Interactive non-button elements must include:
- `role="button"` and `tabIndex={0}`
- `onKeyDown` handler for Enter and Space
- `aria-label` with meaningful description

```tsx
<div
  role="button"
  tabIndex={0}
  onClick={() => handleClick(item)}
  onKeyDown={(e) => { if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') handleClick(item); }}
  aria-label={`${item.name} — ${item.stars} stars`}
>
```

## Types

All shared types live in `src/types/index.ts`. Import with `import type { ... }` (enforced by `verbatimModuleSyntax`).

## Interaction patterns

- **Heatmap day click** → `narrateDay(day)` on the chat store → playful/humorous commentary
- **Repo bar click** → `narrateRepo(repo)` on the chat store → formal, description-focused summary
- **Chat send** → `sendMessage(content)` → stats-aware response via pattern matching

On mobile, after triggering any interaction, auto-scroll/focus to the chat response.
